When a holder‚Äôs bond runs out, the token enters the Liquidation Phase. In this state, the token's price exponentially decays over time, increasing the likelihood of it being bought.
A token's owner sets a price for their own NFT and pays a Harberger-like fee, a Self-Assessed Fee (SAF), proportional to that price. This fee comes out of a bond the owner must post.
